<qti-assessment-item xmlns="http://www.imsglobal.org/xsd/imsqtiasi_v3p0" xmlns:m="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance" identifier="Q41_v3" title="Q41_v3" time-dependent="false" adaptive="false" xsi:schemaLocation="http://www.imsglobal.org/xsd/imsqtiasi_v3p0 https://purl.imsglobal.org/spec/qti/v3p0/schema/xsd/imsqti_asiv3p0_v1p0.xsd">
  <qti-response-declaration identifier="RESPONSE" cardinality="single" base-type="identifier">
    <qti-correct-response>
      <qti-value>ChoiceB</qti-value>
    </qti-correct-response>
  </qti-response-declaration>
  <qti-outcome-declaration identifier="FEEDBACK" cardinality="single" base-type="identifier"/>
  <qti-outcome-declaration identifier="SOLUTION" cardinality="single" base-type="identifier"/>
  <qti-outcome-declaration identifier="SCORE" cardinality="single" base-type="float">
    <qti-default-value>
      <qti-value>0</qti-value>
    </qti-default-value>
  </qti-outcome-declaration>
  <qti-item-body>
    <p>
      En una caja se venden baldosas rectangulares. En la etiqueta se indica que cada baldosa tiene un área de 
      <m:math>
        <m:mn>252</m:mn>
        <m:mtext> </m:mtext>
        <m:msup>
          <m:mi>cm</m:mi>
          <m:mn>2</m:mn>
        </m:msup>
      </m:math>
      y que su ancho mide 4 cm menos que su largo, es decir,
      <m:math>
        <m:mi>ancho</m:mi>
        <m:mo>=</m:mo>
        <m:mi>largo</m:mi>
        <m:mo>-</m:mo>
        <m:mn>4</m:mn>
      </m:math>.
      Se entregan cuatro posibles parejas (largo, ancho) para una baldosa.
    </p>
    <qti-choice-interaction response-identifier="RESPONSE" shuffle="false" max-choices="1">
      <qti-prompt>
        ¿Cuál de las siguientes parejas de medidas, en centímetros, podría corresponder a una baldosa de la caja?
      </qti-prompt>
      
      <qti-simple-choice identifier="ChoiceA">(21 cm, 12 cm)<qti-feedback-inline identifier="FB_ChoiceA" outcome-identifier="FEEDBACK">Incorrecto. Esta pareja tiene el área correcta, porque <m:math><m:mn>21</m:mn><m:mo>×</m:mo><m:mn>12</m:mn><m:mo>=</m:mo><m:mn>252</m:mn></m:math>, pero no cumple la condición del ancho: si el largo es <m:math><m:mn>21</m:mn></m:math>, entonces el ancho debería ser <m:math><m:mn>21</m:mn><m:mo>−</m:mo><m:mn>4</m:mn><m:mo>=</m:mo><m:mn>17</m:mn></m:math>, no <m:math><m:mn>12</m:mn></m:math>.</qti-feedback-inline></qti-simple-choice>
      <qti-simple-choice identifier="ChoiceB">(18 cm, 14 cm)<qti-feedback-inline identifier="FB_ChoiceB" outcome-identifier="FEEDBACK">¡Correcto! Esta pareja cumple las dos condiciones: <m:math><m:mn>18</m:mn><m:mo>×</m:mo><m:mn>14</m:mn><m:mo>=</m:mo><m:mn>252</m:mn></m:math> y además <m:math><m:mn>18</m:mn><m:mo>−</m:mo><m:mn>4</m:mn><m:mo>=</m:mo><m:mn>14</m:mn></m:math>. Por lo tanto, podría corresponder a una baldosa de la caja.</qti-feedback-inline></qti-simple-choice>
      
      <qti-simple-choice identifier="ChoiceC">(16 cm, 12 cm)<qti-feedback-inline identifier="FB_ChoiceC" outcome-identifier="FEEDBACK">Incorrecto. Esta pareja sí cumple que el ancho es 4 cm menor que el largo, porque <m:math><m:mn>16</m:mn><m:mo>−</m:mo><m:mn>4</m:mn><m:mo>=</m:mo><m:mn>12</m:mn></m:math>, pero el área no es la indicada: <m:math><m:mn>16</m:mn><m:mo>×</m:mo><m:mn>12</m:mn><m:mo>=</m:mo><m:mn>192</m:mn></m:math>, y <m:math><m:mn>192</m:mn><m:mo>≠</m:mo><m:mn>252</m:mn></m:math>.</qti-feedback-inline></qti-simple-choice>
      
      <qti-simple-choice identifier="ChoiceD">(17 cm, 13 cm)<qti-feedback-inline identifier="FB_ChoiceD" outcome-identifier="FEEDBACK">Incorrecto. Esta pareja sí cumple que el ancho es 4 cm menor que el largo, porque <m:math><m:mn>17</m:mn><m:mo>−</m:mo><m:mn>4</m:mn><m:mo>=</m:mo><m:mn>13</m:mn></m:math>, pero el área no coincide con la etiqueta: <m:math><m:mn>17</m:mn><m:mo>×</m:mo><m:mn>13</m:mn><m:mo>=</m:mo><m:mn>221</m:mn></m:math>, y <m:math><m:mn>221</m:mn><m:mo>≠</m:mo><m:mn>252</m:mn></m:math>.</qti-feedback-inline></qti-simple-choice>
    </qti-choice-interaction>
    <qti-feedback-block identifier="FB_NoResponse" outcome-identifier="FEEDBACK" show-hide="show">
      <qti-content-body>
        <p>No se seleccionó ninguna alternativa. Para resolver el problema, hay que revisar cuál pareja cumple simultáneamente estas dos condiciones:</p>
        <p>
          <m:math>
            <m:mi>largo</m:mi>
            <m:mo>×</m:mo>
            <m:mi>ancho</m:mi>
            <m:mo>=</m:mo>
            <m:mn>252</m:mn>
          </m:math>
          y
          <m:math>
            <m:mi>ancho</m:mi>
            <m:mo>=</m:mo>
            <m:mi>largo</m:mi>
            <m:mo>−</m:mo>
            <m:mn>4</m:mn>
          </m:math>.
        </p>
        <p>La alternativa correcta es <strong>(18 cm, 14 cm)</strong>.</p>
      </qti-content-body>
    </qti-feedback-block>
    <qti-feedback-block identifier="show" outcome-identifier="SOLUTION" show-hide="show">
      <qti-content-body>
        <p><strong>Resolución paso a paso</strong></p>
        <ol>
          <li>
            <p><strong>Paso 1: Revisar las dos condiciones del problema</strong></p>
            <p>La pareja correcta debe cumplir simultáneamente:</p>
            <p>Área de la baldosa:
              <m:math>
                <m:mi>largo</m:mi>
                <m:mtext> </m:mtext>
                <m:mo>×</m:mo>
                <m:mtext> </m:mtext>
                <m:mi>ancho</m:mi>
                <m:mo>=</m:mo>
                <m:mn>252</m:mn>
              </m:math>
            </p>
            <p>Y además:
              <m:math>
                <m:mi>ancho</m:mi>
                <m:mo>=</m:mo>
                <m:mi>largo</m:mi>
                <m:mo>−</m:mo>
                <m:mn>4</m:mn>
              </m:math>
            </p>
          </li>
          <li>
            <p><strong>Paso 2: Probar cada alternativa</strong></p>
            <p><em>Opción A:</em> <m:math><m:mn>21</m:mn><m:mo>×</m:mo><m:mn>12</m:mn><m:mo>=</m:mo><m:mn>252</m:mn></m:math>, pero <m:math><m:mn>21</m:mn><m:mo>−</m:mo><m:mn>4</m:mn><m:mo>=</m:mo><m:mn>17</m:mn></m:math>. El ancho debería ser 17, no 12. No sirve.</p>
            <p><em>Opción B:</em> <m:math><m:mn>18</m:mn><m:mo>×</m:mo><m:mn>14</m:mn><m:mo>=</m:mo><m:mn>252</m:mn></m:math> y además <m:math><m:mn>18</m:mn><m:mo>−</m:mo><m:mn>4</m:mn><m:mo>=</m:mo><m:mn>14</m:mn></m:math>. Sí cumple ambas condiciones.</p>
            <p><em>Opción C:</em> <m:math><m:mn>16</m:mn><m:mo>−</m:mo><m:mn>4</m:mn><m:mo>=</m:mo><m:mn>12</m:mn></m:math>, pero <m:math><m:mn>16</m:mn><m:mo>×</m:mo><m:mn>12</m:mn><m:mo>=</m:mo><m:mn>192</m:mn></m:math>. El área no es 252. No sirve.</p>
            <p><em>Opción D:</em> <m:math><m:mn>17</m:mn><m:mo>−</m:mo><m:mn>4</m:mn><m:mo>=</m:mo><m:mn>13</m:mn></m:math>, pero <m:math><m:mn>17</m:mn><m:mo>×</m:mo><m:mn>13</m:mn><m:mo>=</m:mo><m:mn>221</m:mn></m:math>. El área no es 252. No sirve.</p>
          </li>
          <li>
            <p><strong>Paso 3: Concluir</strong></p>
            <p>La única pareja que cumple al mismo tiempo el área <m:math><m:mn>252</m:mn><m:mtext> </m:mtext><m:msup><m:mi>cm</m:mi><m:mn>2</m:mn></m:msup></m:math> y la relación <m:math><m:mi>ancho</m:mi><m:mo>=</m:mo><m:mi>largo</m:mi><m:mo>−</m:mo><m:mn>4</m:mn></m:math> es <strong>(18 cm, 14 cm)</strong>.</p>
          </li>
        </ol>
      </qti-content-body>
    </qti-feedback-block>
  </qti-item-body>
  <qti-response-processing>
    <qti-response-condition>
      <qti-response-if>
        <qti-match>
          <qti-variable identifier="RESPONSE"/>
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">ChoiceB</qti-base-value>
        </qti-match>
        <qti-set-outcome-value identifier="SCORE">
          <qti-base-value base-type="float">1</qti-base-value>
        </qti-set-outcome-value>
        <qti-set-outcome-value identifier="FEEDBACK">
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">FB_ChoiceB</qti-base-value>
        </qti-set-outcome-value>
        <qti-set-outcome-value identifier="SOLUTION">
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">show</qti-base-value>
        </qti-set-outcome-value>
      </qti-response-if>
      <qti-response-else-if>
        <qti-match>
          <qti-variable identifier="RESPONSE"/>
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">ChoiceA</qti-base-value>
        </qti-match>
        <qti-set-outcome-value identifier="FEEDBACK">
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">FB_ChoiceA</qti-base-value>
        </qti-set-outcome-value>
        <qti-set-outcome-value identifier="SOLUTION">
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">show</qti-base-value>
        </qti-set-outcome-value>
      </qti-response-else-if>
      <qti-response-else-if>
        <qti-match>
          <qti-variable identifier="RESPONSE"/>
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">ChoiceC</qti-base-value>
        </qti-match>
        <qti-set-outcome-value identifier="FEEDBACK">
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">FB_ChoiceC</qti-base-value>
        </qti-set-outcome-value>
        <qti-set-outcome-value identifier="SOLUTION">
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">show</qti-base-value>
        </qti-set-outcome-value>
      </qti-response-else-if>
      <qti-response-else-if>
        <qti-match>
          <qti-variable identifier="RESPONSE"/>
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">ChoiceD</qti-base-value>
        </qti-match>
        <qti-set-outcome-value identifier="FEEDBACK">
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">FB_ChoiceD</qti-base-value>
        </qti-set-outcome-value>
        <qti-set-outcome-value identifier="SOLUTION">
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">show</qti-base-value>
        </qti-set-outcome-value>
      </qti-response-else-if>
      <qti-response-else>
        <qti-set-outcome-value identifier="FEEDBACK">
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">FB_NoResponse</qti-base-value>
        </qti-set-outcome-value>
        <qti-set-outcome-value identifier="SOLUTION">
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">show</qti-base-value>
        </qti-set-outcome-value>
      </qti-response-else>
    </qti-response-condition>
  </qti-response-processing>
</qti-assessment-item>